<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1117">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.1123/56.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The First Chief informed me this morning that the <hi rend="italic">Bravo</hi> went to Tampico instead of Progreso, but that two
                            gunboats would be sent to latter place, as it the Government’s
                            determination to keep the port closed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>